    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is an old question but for anyone stumbling across it (like I did):</p>\n<ol>\n<li>from 3.4.0 Mockito can mock static methods, look to the MockStatic class for details.</li>\n<li>The capture fails because of times(): verify focuses first on counting the number of times, and it can't capture from potentially multiple calls.</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 36934717,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 27994093,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3843fa19bae66e52dbaf9c4285daea0a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jesse",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/27994093/jesse"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1760200940,
    "creation_date" : 1760200940,
    "answer_id" : 79788128,
    "question_id" : 52634895,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>MockedStatic&lt;StaticClass&gt; mocked = mockStatic(StaticClass.class)\nArgumentCaptor&lt;String&gt; captor = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(String.class);\nmocked.verify(() -&gt; StaticClass.staticMethod(captor.capture()));\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
